    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="838"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d838">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.2222/12596</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-02T13:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6.39 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1796. Your telegram 1089,<note n="3" xml:id="d838fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_693">p. 693</ref>.</note>
                    received 18th [<hi rend="italic">February 28?</hi>] and my despatch No. 917,
                    June 4.<note n="4" xml:id="d838fn4">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office today
                    communicates following: Tax ruled in Italy for exemption military service cannot
                    be <pb facs="0790" n="706" xml:id="pg_706"/> levied on those Italian citizens
                    found to have no longer the status of shirker or deserter, and [who] do military
                    service in American Army. As a result said Italian citizens are able to obtain
                    complete remittal of the tax provided they have certificate from American
                    military authorities to the effect that they are serving in American Army. Full
                    details by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
